Privacy Addendum for California Residents
Information We Collect and How it is Used
We may automatically collect information when you visit the Site including your device’s IP address, and statistics about how you use the Site. If you connect with the Site through a link in an email we may automatically collect your email address and associate it with other statistical information about your access to and use of the Site.
We may collect information that you submit when visiting the Site including product registration information (your name, email and postal address, telephone number, product information, and user name and password) or contact information if you sign up for our newsletter or contact us with an inquiry (name, email address, telephone number). If you submit a comment or suggestion or communicate with us through the Site we may collect and retain the information you submit. Information that you submit may be linked with statistical information about your access to and use of the Site.
We may use your personal information for our general commercial purposes, including, for example:
to process your transactions;
to contact you about products you have purchased or customer service;
to respond to your inquiries;
to contact you with your permission by email or postal mail to inform you of products and service opportunities that may be of interest to you,  new KIOXIA updates or offerings, upcoming events or trade show, or customer surveys;
to display advertisements relevant to your interests;
to conduct market research regarding KIOXIA products or services;
to learn how and when you access or use our Site or the information we provide online;
to customize the content of the Site for you; and
to support and enhance our communications with you.
Access to Your Information and Opting Out
If you provided information through a registration process such as to download content or receive our newsletters, you may opt out of receiving our newsletters or other marketing information from us by clicking
here
and unsubscribing. Or, you may opt out by using the unsubscribe link on any email you receive from us. If you opt out of receiving our newsletters or other marketing information, we may still send you certain types of communications, such as product updates for your registered products, transactional or legal notification emails, warranty related communications and we may respond to requests from you by email. If you opt-out through one of these methods we will try to process your request in a timely manner.
Some jurisdictions allow you to request a copy of the information we hold about you or other additional rights. Requests can be made by contacting us at the address below and providing contact information and information that establishes your identity. We will endeavor to respond within a timely manner in accordance with your local laws upon receipt of your completed request. In some cases we may charge a fee for providing this information.
For California residents, further opt-out information is contained in the California Addendum at the end of this document.
Sharing of Personal Information
We do not sell your personal information as traditionally understood. Please note some jurisdictions may have a non-traditional and/or broader definition of “sell.” We may share your personal information in compliance with local laws, for example, with KIOXIA group companies for business purposes and with other companies who provide marketing or other services on our behalf and at our direction, but we generally do not permit them to use such personal information that we have shared for their own direct marketing purposes.
Your personal information may be shared with third parties that provide services to KIOXIA (such as analyzing data, providing customer support, product registration, etc.), to the extent that such information is necessary for providing such services to you, and where such sharing is permitted under local laws. This may include distributors and sales representatives through which we sell our products. KIOXIA seeks contractual arrangements with these KIOXIA Providers under which these KIOXIA Providers agree not to disclose any information we provide to them. Other than such third parties, KIOXIA will not share your information with anyone who is not an employee of KIOXIA or an affiliate with a need to access the information for business purposes, or who has not signed an appropriate non-disclosure agreement except under the special circumstances provided in this Privacy Policy.
Your personal information may be shared with unaffiliated third parties under the following special circumstances:
(1) if you request or authorize it;
(2) if the information is provided to help complete a transaction for you;
(3) if the information is provided to comply with the law, applicable regulations, governmental and quasi-governmental requests, court orders or subpoenas, to enforce our Terms of Use or other agreements, or to protect our rights, property or safety or the rights, property or safety of our users or others (e.g., to a consumer reporting agency for fraud protection etc.); or
(4) if the disclosure is done as part of a purchase, transfer or sale of services or assets (e.g., in the event that substantially all of our assets are acquired by another party, customer information may be one of the transferred assets).
We may disclose your non-private, aggregated, or otherwise non-personally identifiable information, such as usage statistics of our Site or products, to our affiliates and third parties.
Cookies and Various Technologies
We use technology to help us deliver customized visitor experiences and understand trends and patterns. We use first and third-party cookies on our websites, in order to measure and analyze performance and usage, enhance user experiences, personalize content and ads, and provide social media and other third-party features.
We may use or engage third parties to collect non-personal information using cookies and/or other industry standard technologies (e.g., clear GIFS, web beacons, pixel tags, javascript tag) to, for example, generate statistics or measure and analyze website activity (including page usage and paths followed during visits through our sites) in order to improve Site functionality, deliver content specific to you and/or targeted for your interests while using the Site and/or a third party web site, and to better manage advertising of our products. The collected data also helps us determine which product, service or support information may be appropriate for you.
A cookie is a small text file that the website sends to your device for the purpose of keeping records. It identifies your device, typically your web browser, but it solely cannot identify you as an individual. We may use temporary cookies (“session”) to grant Site visitors access to content and to enable commenting—actions they must be logged in to perform. These cookies expire and are automatically erased whenever you close your browser. We may also use long-term (“persistent”) cookies to better understand usage patterns so we can improve the site for our customers. We use a persistent cookie to remember that you closed the cookie disclosure banner giving your consent to receive cookies, but this only works when cookies on our site are enabled. Persistent cookies usually have an expiration date in the distant future and remain in your browser until they expire or you manually delete them.
In order to provide you a more personalized user experience, we may collect information about your online activities over time and also your activities on third party web sites, for example, via analytics and personalization cookies. Our website may use Google Analytics. For more information please visit:
www.google.com/policies/privacy/partners/
.
We do not respond to “do not track” signals, if any, being sent from your browser. However, we do respond to Global Privacy Control (GPC) requests, which may be automatically transmitted by your browser. We may permit select third parties to collect non-personal information about your online activities over time and across different web sites when you use the Site.
You can choose whether to allow us or third-parties (e.g., our Adtech partners) to set cookies which are not strictly necessary for the functioning of the website via the  “Do Not Sell or Share My Information” link and settings provided on the individual websites. If you would like to review and manage your cookie preferences, including opting-out of any of the technologies that we and/or our third parties employ to collect your information via the Site that are not strictly necessary, you may do so by clicking
here
or by clicking on the “Do Not Sell or Share My Information” link at the bottom of our website. However, if you opt out of non-essential cookies, some areas of our site may not function properly. Cookies and similar technologies may be associated with other information about you. Please note that your cookie preferences are browser and device specific. So, if you come back to this website from a different device or browser, or delete cookies on your current browser, you will need to apply these settings again. In addition, if you access a different KIOXIA website or domain, you may also need to apply your settings for that website as well.
Retention Period
We will retain your personal information for the period necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Policy unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law.
Sensitive Information
KIOXIA does not seek to collect your sensitive personal information. We ask that you do not send us or disclose any sensitive personal information (e.g., Social Security numbers, information related to racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religion or other beliefs, health, biometrics or genetic characteristics, criminal background or trade union membership) on or through the Site to us.
Children's Privacy
This Site is not directed to or intended to be used by children under the age of 18. KIOXIA does not knowingly collect personal information about children through the Site. If you are under the age of 18, please do not provide any personally identifiable information to us through this Site.
International Visitors
This Site is operated in Japan and the United States of America, information you submit to us is stored on servers located in Japan and the United States, and information on the website is intended for users accessing the website from North/South America. If you are visiting from a location outside North/South America, your information may be processed by us in Japan and the United States, where laws regarding data protection may be less stringent than the laws in your country. Users outside of the North/South America are directed to use their respective regional websites. By using this Site and by providing any personal information to the Site, all users fully understand and unambiguously consent to the collection and processing of such information in Japan and the United States.
Notification of Changes
From time to time, we may choose to change our Privacy Policy. We will notify you of material changes to this Privacy Policy by posting a revised Privacy Policy on the Site with an updated effective date. Any updates, revisions, supplements, modifications or amendments to this Privacy Policy shall be effective immediately upon its posting. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy regularly for any changes. Your continued use of this Site and your continued provision of personally identifiable information to us will be subject to the terms of the then-current Privacy Policy.
Protecting your Information
We have implemented reasonable physical, electronic and administrative security measures and practices in an effort to protect the security, integrity and confidentiality of your personal information. However, no security system is 100% secure. It may be possible for third parties to intercept or access information that you provide to KIOXIA or its third party KIOXIA Providers. We cannot guarantee the security of your information, nor can we guarantee that information you supply will not be intercepted while being transmitted. However, KIOXIA will comply with all laws and regulations related to data security and breach response.
It is important for you to protect against unauthorized access to your personal information. If you have reason to believe that your interaction with us is no longer secure, please immediately notify us of the problem by contacting us in accordance with the "Contact Us" page.
Links to Third-Party Sites
When you use the Site, you may be directed to other websites that are beyond our control. These may include sites where you register products that you have purchased. We may also allow thirds-party sites or applications to link to the Site. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of any third parties or the content of linked sites except where specifically stated, but we do encourage you to read the applicable privacy policies and terms and conditions of such parties or web sites. This Privacy Policy only applies to our Sites.
We will not share your information with third parties for their direct marketing purposes unless you provide consent.
