Use of Personal Information
KIOXIA may use, or disclose the personal information we collect for one or more of the following purposes:
To fulfill or meet the reason you provided the information, or at your direction.
To provide you with support and to respond to your inquiries, including to investigate and address your concerns and monitor and improve our responses.
To respond to law enforcement requests and as required by applicable law, court order, or governmental regulations.
As described to you when collecting your personal information or as otherwise set forth in the CCPA/CPRA.
KIOXIA will not collect additional categories of personal information or use the personal information we collected for materially different, unrelated, or incompatible purposes without providing you notice.
Sale of Personal Information
The CCPA/CPRA defines a "sale" as disclosing or making available to a third party personal information in exchange for monetary or other valuable consideration. While we do not disclose personal information to third parties in exchange for monetary compensation from such third parties, we may disclose or make available certain categories of personal information to third parties in order to receive certain services or benefits from them, such as when we make browsing history available to third-party ad companies (through third-party tags on our website) in order to improve and measure our ad campaigns and reach users with more relevant ads and content. To the extent that this constitutes a sale as defined by the CCPA/CPRA, we may "sell" identifiers and usage data to third-party advertising networks, analytics providers, and social networks.
California residents have the right to opt-out of our sale of their personal information. We do not sell personal information about residents who we know are younger than 16 years old. You may opt out of "sales" (via third-party cookies) on our websites, by clicking
here
or by clicking on the “Do Not Sell or Share My Information” link at the bottom of our website.
Disclosure of Personal Information to Third Parties
KIOXIA may disclose your personal information to a third party for a business purpose. However, prior to any disclosure of your personal information for a business purpose, KIOXIA will execute a contract with the third party receiving your personal information that describes the purpose, and requires the recipient to act in compliance with the contract.
KIOXIA shares your personal information with the following categories of third parties:
KIOXIA Providers.
Parent company and/or sister companies.
